">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">Phil Gingrey</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">R-11</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$15,800,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$48,537,750</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$29,696,500</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$94,034,250</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">John Barrow</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">D-12</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$5,350,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$15,046,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$21,280,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$41,676,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">David Scott</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">D-13</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$38,828,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$27,940,500</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$13,432,500</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">$80,201,000</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">Tom Graves</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">R-14</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td style=\"vertical-align:bottom\">\r\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>Source: Open Secrets website</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To double-check our numbers, we reached out to Taxpayers for Common Sense, who provides the raw data for the searchable Open Secrets site. The nonprofit, with staffers who have worked for both Democrats and Republicans, shows slightly different tallies for those years &ndash; but comes to the same broad conclusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It counts 146 earmarks from Kingston, totaling about $213 million. That compares with $116 million in earmarks from the other six GOP congressmen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kingston, who represents five of Georgia&rsquo;s eight military installations, noted that much of the funding was for defense or military spending such as an IED simulator at Fort Stewart and hospital renovations at installations statewide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kingston contrasted that record with Perdue&rsquo;s, whose business record includes a brief leadership of Pillowtex, a troubled North Carolina textile firm that went under shortly after he left.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;The majority of what we did was for the military,&quot; Kingston said. &quot;I don&rsquo;t know that we need lectures on fiscal responsibility from somebody with his abysmal track record.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In isolation, those costs don&rsquo;t appear to be a problem, said Steve Ellis, the vice president of Taxpayers For Common Sense. But money spent there is money not available for other projects that may be more critical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But without the procurement process that follows other federal spending, there&rsquo;s no way to judge the merit of the projects being funded, he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;If a congressman is saying they know their district better than a pointed-headed bureaucrat, that&rsquo;s absolutely true,&quot; Ellis said. &quot;But with earmarks, they&rsquo;re saying they know what&rsquo;s best for all 435 congressional districts. And that&rsquo;s not true at all.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perdue said Kingston had more earmarks than any other congressman in the state and more than Georgia&rsquo;s other GOP congressmen combined.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Two separate databases back him up. It&rsquo;s up to voters to decide whether that&rsquo;s a good thing or a bad thing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is one caveat to Perdue&rsquo;s claim. It covers three years, and Kingston has been in office for two decades. It&rsquo;s that bit of context that moves it down just a notch on the Truth-O-Meter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We rate Perdue&rsquo;s statement Mostly True.</p>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2014-06-30T14:02:40.301525", "ruling_date": "2014-07-01T00:00:00", "ruling_headline": "Does Kingston bring home the bacon?", "ruling_headline_slug": "does-kingston-bring-home-bacon", "ruling_link_text": "Good or bad, Kingston a leader with earmarks", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>David Perdue <a href=\"https://twitter.com/perduesenate\"><strong>Twitter </strong></a>account</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interview with David Perdue, June 26, 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interview with Jack Kingston June 27, 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Center for Responsive Politics earmarks <a href=\"http://www.opensecrets.org/earmarks/index.php?cycle=2007&amp;type=S\"><strong>database</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taxpayers for Common Sense earmarks <a href=\"http://www.taxpayer.net/library/article/earmark-and-appropriations-data\"><strong>database</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, &quot;State delegation split over &#39;no-pork&#39; <a href=\"http://www.myajc.com/news/news/state-regional-govt-politics/state-delegation-split-over-no-pork-pledge/ngThB/\"><strong>pledge</strong></a>,&quot; July 25, 2008</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interview with Taxpayers for Common Sense Vice President Steve Ellis, June 26, 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 5, "current_job": "U.S. Senate candidate", "false_count": 1, "first_name": "David", "half_true_count": 5, "home_state": "Georgia", "id": 2602, "last_name": "Perdue", "mostly_true_count": 8, "name_slug": "david-perdue", "pants_count": 1, "party": {"id": 3, "party": "Republican", "party_slug": "republican", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/3/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/mugs/David_Perdue.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Georgia", "edition": "Georgia", "edition_slug": "georgia", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 5, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Georgia Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/5/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/2602/", "total_count": 20, "true_count": 0, "website": "https://perduesenate.com/"}, "statement": "<p>U.S. Senate candidate Jack Kingston &quot;requested more earmarks than any other GA Congressman and all GA GOP members combined.&quot;</p>\r\n", "statement_context": "In a Twitter post", "statement_date": "2014-06-23", "statement_type": {"id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementtype/2/", "statement_type": "Claim", "type_description": "blog post "}, "subject": [{"description": "", "id": 33, "photo": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/33/", "subject": "Feder